Name: Nusr-Et Steakhouse New York
Description: Outpost of a high-end international steakhouse chain by a chef known for his dramatic serving style.

Name: The Lobster Club
Description: High-end Japanese locale serving sushi & teppanyaki dishes in a sophisticated, lounge-style setting.

Name: DaDong New York
Description: Spacious branch of a Chinese chain devoted to upscale roast duck, with tasting menus & a terrace.

Name: Ferris
Description: Sleek yet cozy New American in the MADE Hotel offering seasonal, eclectic dishes & drinks.

Name: L'Atelier and Le Grill de Joel Robuchon
Description: Place for modern French dishes & tasting menus (including vegetarian) from an acclaimed chef.

Name: Miznon
Description: Chelsea Market branch of a global chain for Mediterranean stuffed pitas with a local twist.

Name: Cote Korean Steakhouse
Description: Guests cook their own dry-aged steaks on tabletop grills at this upscale Korean spot.

Name: Scampi
Description: Chic space for Southern Italian seafood, pastas & wine, with banquette & communal seating.

Name: Don Angie
Description: Place for updated Italian-American classics with wine & cocktails in a marble-accented space.

Name: Sorbillo Pizzeria
Description: Full-service pizza place by a Neapolitan pizzaiolo, also offering salads, pastas, beer & wine.

Name: Name
Description: Description

Name: Statue of Liberty
Description: Iconic National Monument opened in 1886, offering guided tours, a museum & city views.

Name: Central Park
Description: Sprawling park with pedestrian paths & ballfields, plus a zoo, carousel, boat rentals & a reservoir.

Name: Rockefeller Center and Top of the Rock Observation Deck
Description: Observatory on top of Rockefeller Center, with an ocean-liner style design, offering city views.

Name: Metropolitan Museum of Art
Description: A grand setting for one of the world's greatest collections of art, from ancient to contemporary.

Name: Time Square
Description: Bustling destination in the heart of the Theater District known for bright lights, shopping & shows.

Name: Empire State Building
Description: Iconic, art deco office tower from 1931 with exhibits & observatories on the 86th & 102nd floors.

Name: ¾High Line
Description: Popular park 30 feet above street level on an old rail line, with river & city views.

Name: Brooklyn Bridge
Description: Beloved, circa-1883 landmark connecting Manhattan & Brooklyn via a unique stone-&-steel design.

Name: Wall Street
Description: This street and the surrounding area are home to some of the most important exchanges in the world, including the New York Stock Exchange, the NASDAQ, and the New York Mercantile Exchange.

Name: Grand Central Terminal
Description: Iconic train station known for its grand facade & main concourse, also offering shops & dining.
